[[File:PE-mapa-Itaíba.png|thumb|right|300px|Location of Itaíba within Pernambuco.]] '''Itaíba''' is a city located in the state of [[Pernambuco]], [[Brazil]]. It is located 306&nbsp;km away from [[Recife]], the capital of the state of Pernambuco. It has an estimated ([[Brazilian Institute of Geography and Statistics|Ibge 2009]]) population of 27,631 inhabitants.
==Geography== * State - [[Pernambuco]] * Region - [[Agreste|Agreste Pernambucano]] * Boundaries - [[Tupanatinga]] ('''N'''); [[Alagoas]] state ('''S'''); [[Buique]] and [[Águas Belas]] ('''E'''); [[Manari, Pernambuco|Manari]] and Alagoas [[States of Brazil|state]] ('''W'''). * Area - 1068.29&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup> * Elevation - 478 m * Hidrography - [[Ipanema River]] * Vegetation - [[Caatinga]] [[Hiperxerófila]] * Clima - [[Semi arid]] hot * Annual average temperature - 24.1 c * Distance to [[Recife]] - 331&nbsp;km
==Economy== The main economic activities in '''Itaíba''' are based in [[agribusiness]], especially [[beans]], [[maize|corn]]; and [[livestock]] such as [[cattle]] (over 83,000 heads), [[goats]], [[sheep]], [[pigs]], [[horses]] and [[poultry]].
